messages.text: My dad has a secret gf, named Lisa...
who was with him the night of the accident.
I found her # & chatted w/ her.
That they are only "friends"  but I think otherwise.
She said he spilled something & went to her place to clean up
but after the accident he came back from the hospital w/out his jacket
So I went to his cleaners & found it.
Please don't tell me what kind of stain you expected to find. Gross!
Inside his pocket was a cocktail napkin with the name of the bar...
I went to the bar, spoke with the bartender
Fortunately I know him pretty well
He said he saw both of them arguing with another man
He didn't hear, or didn't want to say.
Truth is, he's kinda a fuck-up.
But I'm gonna confront Lisa about it.
Wait, what did Lisa's note say?
Just some #s... can't figure it out.
And why is she such a secret? I thought your parents separated.
He has to keep her secret so it doesn't damage his reelection.
The voters like their candidates married -- with no cheating...
And there's another thing that's really spooky
My bar friend's job is also to rotate the surveillance videos
But the next day when he went to the office to reset the tapes
They're not really tapes, but removable SD cards
and the one from that night was gone from the recorder.
I don't want you getting hurt.
If you do, I'll kill you!!
Didn't you once tell me that you wished your dad would disappear?
One time I said that I wanted him to hide away from the world.
He's always been a soft touch. Everyone takes advantage of him.
He's given so much money to so many people who never repay him
that we had to borrow money from the bank just to pay rent and food.
But you wouldn't mind if he was locked away?
I may feel that now and then
but I would NEVER want to see it happen.
So work with me on this.
What do you want from me?
Help me find out what really happened that night.
I'm not a detective. And neither are you!
But you can get access to your dad's phone...
but my dad and Claude were texting about the shaky finances of the campaign.
And this hurts my heart to say,
but my dad was begging for money!
things are a lot worse than I thought.
a couple days after the accident, my dad sent just one message to Claude
that's the same as Lisa wrote
What r u going to do?
then see if that reporter can help decypher them.
Those numbers are for two different bank accounts.
Give me some time to research it and I'll get right back to you.
Lisa, I got to speak with you.
I told you to go away.
But I don't want to text you about it.
It's about something you wrote on a cocktail napkin.
when you were at the Centerville Bar
Stop texting right now and meet me there in 1 hr
I was meeting her at the bar, when she went out to smoke
She left her purse, wallet, ID...
